{"id": "fh91x6", "title": "Cintas (CTAS) Puts", "selftext": "From their 10K, Cintas provides Uniform Rental and Facility Services and First Aid and Safety Services. Within these segments Cintas provides:\n\n* **The Uniform Rental and Facility Services** ($5.5B)- Rental and servicing of uniforms and other garments, including flame resistant clothing, mats, mops and shop towels, restroom cleaning services and supplies, and carpet and tile cleaning services\n* **First Aid and Safety Services** ($0.6B) **-** fire extinguishers and testing, and safety and compliance training.\n\nThe company's 10-K also mentions major risk factors for their business including:\n\n* ***Negative global economic factors may adversely affect our financial performance*** *-* With the coronavirus major sporting and music events are being canceled meaning reduction in event staff and janitorial staff. This reduction directly affects Cintas' core Uniform and Facility Service business. Not to mention other industries already affected that rely on their services such as airlines and cruise companies, \n* ***Changes in the fuel and energy industry could adversely affect our financial condition and results of operations****. -* Reduced demand for US Shale oil due to the price war and travel restrictions/demand will result in a reduction of oil field and refinery workers who rely on flame retardant uniforms and related supplies that Cintas makes. Additionally less demand for oil field contractors will lessen the demand for their fire and safety compliance training divisions.\n* ***Risks associated with the suppliers from whom our products are sourced could adversely affect our results of operations****. -* Cintas sources its products through a large chain of global suppliers. The coronavirus is likely to have a severe effect on their ability to source their products.\n\nCintas is the next major domino to fall due to the virus/price war: **4/17 CTAS $200P**", "created_utc": 1583979400.0, "permalink": "